# Read docs/ before working on this project

**Do not write or change code until you have read the relevant documentation.** This repo is designed to be executable without tribal knowledge. The `docs/` folder is the source of truth for what to build, why, and how.

## Mandatory first step

1. List `docs/` and skim `docs/00-EXECUTIVE-SUMMARY.md` §7 (documentation index) and §3 (locked decisions).
2. Read the docs that apply to your task (see table below). For new features or unfamiliar areas, read **all** of `docs/` in order before coding.
3. Check `plans/` for the current phase, stage, and open checkboxes — tick progress in the same PR that completes the work.

## Reading order (full pass)

| Doc | When you need it |
|---|---|
| `00-EXECUTIVE-SUMMARY.md` | Always — context, locked decisions, risks |
| `01-REQUIREMENTS-PRD.md` | Requirements, personas, traceability matrix |
| `02-ARCHITECTURE.md` | Stack, deployment, integrations, repo layout |
| `03-DATABASE-SCHEMA.md` | Any schema, migration, or query work |
| `04-MODULE-SPECS.md` | Business logic (attendance, leave, payroll, workflows) |
| `05-UIUX-SPEC.md` | Frontend, design tokens, Warm Editorial UI |
| `06-REPORTS-AND-DASHBOARDS.md` | Reports, exports, CEO dashboard KPIs |
| `07-ROADMAP.md` | Phasing, sequencing, cut-over, risks |
| `08-ROLES-AND-PERMISSIONS.md` | RBAC, roles, approval chains, navigation |
| `09-GREYTHR-RECON-FINDINGS.md` | Parity targets from live greytHR recon |
| `10-INDIA-PAYROLL-STATUTORY-REFERENCE.md` | Statutory rates, formulas, golden tests |
| `11-EXISTING-EMS-YATRA-AVEDAN.md` | T&E absorption (Phase 3.5) |
| `12-VISUAL-REFERENCE-CREXTIO.md` | Design feel and visual direction |
| `13-MASTER-BUILD-PLAN.md` | Executable steps, gates, scale posture |
| `14-TECH-STACK-AND-RELIABILITY.md` | Stack decisions, reliability program, testing |

**Conflict rule:** where `14-TECH-STACK-AND-RELIABILITY.md` conflicts with `02-ARCHITECTURE.md`, **doc 14 wins**.

## Execution workflow

- **Specs:** `docs/` — what and why
- **Tracker:** `plans/` — current phase, stages, gates, checkboxes (`plans/README.md` for how to use)
- **PRs:** cite requirement IDs (`feat: ATT-08 …`); no orphan features
- **Policy values:** never hardcode — read from `core.settings` (doc 04 §8)
- **Money/payroll:** test-first with golden fixtures (docs 04 §6.9, 10 §13); human review mandatory on payroll-core changes

## Repo layout (from doc 02)

```
frontend/   # React — tokens + ui kit live here
backend/    # Express + TypeScript modules
docs/       # specifications (read first)
plans/      # live execution tracker
```

Frontend and backend are **independent projects** with an API-first contract (typed RPC + OpenAPI). Money math exists **only** in the backend.
